edu.umass.cs.msocket.gns

Class Integration

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.msocket.gns.Integration

  • public class Integration
extends Object
    This class defines the methods used for the integration with the GNS. All interactions to store and retrieve information to/from the GNS are defined. here.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Emmanuel Cecchet

      • registerWithGNS

        public static void registerWithGNS(String name,
                                   InetSocketAddress saddr)
                            throws IOException
        Register any globally unique Human Readable Name in the GNS and create a field with the same name in that GUID to store the InetSocketAddress information.
        Parameters:
        name - Human readable name of the service (needs to be unique GNS-wide)
        saddr - The IP address to store for this service
        credentials - The GNS credentials to use, usually the account GUID and default GNS (if null default GNS credentials are used)
        Throws:
        IOException

      • getSocketAddressFromGNS

        public static List<InetSocketAddress> getSocketAddressFromGNS(String name)
                                                       throws UnknownHostException
        Lookup the IP address(es) of an MServerSocket by its Human Readable Name registered in the GNS. throws UnknownHostException, so that it is similar to exception thrown on DNS failure
        Parameters:
        name - Human readable name of the MServerSocket
        gnsCredentials - GNS credentials to use
        Returns:
        list of IP addresses or null if not found
        Throws:
        Exception
        UnknownHostException

      • unregisterWithGNS

        public static void unregisterWithGNS(String name)
                              throws IOException
        Clear the list contained in the given field name from the GNS.
        Parameters:
        name - field name to clear
        gnsCredentials - GNS access credentials
        Throws:
        Exception - if a GNS error occurs
        IOException

        Parameters:
